The Chairman, Kano Concerned Citizens Initiative (KCCI), Alhaji Bashir Othman Tofa, has urged Governor Abdullahi Ganduje of Kano State to shun all forms of vindictiveness as he prepares to govern for a second term of four years. Alhaji Tofa, in a statement signed and issued in Kano, urged the governor to embrace all people of Kano as one family. “They must pursue the agenda for development they shared with KCCI during our interactions with candidates,” he said. He lauded Governor Ganduje’s call for peace and thanked the Emir of Kano, Malam Muhammad Sanusi ll, for his constant calls for peace throughout the election period. Kano guber rerun: Tofa warns against violence 2019: MY VOTE IS… (10) FOR KANO ELDERS I will concede defeat if I fail—Ganduje